The paper involves the use of LSTM recurrent neural networks and ARIMA models for predicting stock price correlation coefficients. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves financial modeling and time series analysis, which could place it in the computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also involves statistical modeling and analysis, which could place it in the mathematical aspects (cs.MA) sub-category.
